identificationRemarks: I am always pleased to see the rocky crevice habitat included in the observation! I included the ssp. diversifolia because the greater length - width ratio of this race, over the ssp. micrantha, seen in at least in the Columbia River Gorge, and somewhere to the north of that. Possibly all of the observations I've seen in SE Vancouver Island and greater Vancouver, BC, have been this race. These longer leaves also help distinguish this species from Tellima grandiflora - Fringe-cups.
